      "message": "I took a look at this function in SkMatrix and it doesn\u0027t guard against w \u003c 0 when it projects to 2D. When w \u003c 0 we should skip the small path renderer too, I\u0027d think. In most situations with w \u003c 0, I\u0027d bet the mapRectToQuad bounds would exceed area/baseArea \u003e 4.\n\nIf we accept some approximations to the device area, we could do GrQuad::MakeFromRect(bounds, args.fViewMatrix) and then call GrQuad::bounds(). This projects and clips to w \u003e epsilon, but we\u0027re switching to using the device-space bounding box\u0027s area instead of the quad\u0027s area.\n\nAnother option would be to convert the SkRect to SkPoint3\u0027s and call SkMatrix::mapHomogeneousPoints, check w and return CanDrawPath::kNo if any w \u003c\u003d 0. If w \u003e 0 for every corner, divide by w and proceed as you\u0027ve already written for the exact quad area.\n\nWDYT?",
